Citation.sTitle: Excess volumes and partial molar volumes of binary mixtures of 1,2-propanediol carbonate with xylene in the temperature range of (293.15 to 353.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: The densities of binary mixtures formed by 1,2-propanediol carbonate with o-xylene, or m-xylene, or p-xylene were measured in the temperature range of (293.15 to 353.15) K and atmospheric pressure using a vibrating-tube densimeter. The excess molar volumes V E m, partial molar volumes and excess partial molar volumes of two components calculated from the density data provide the temperature dependence. The V E m results were correlated using the fourth-order Redlich Kister equation, with the maximum likelihood principle being applied for the determination of the adjustable parameters. It was found that the V E m in these systems studied increases with rising temperature.
